column5: It's been snowing here in east Wisconsin since November and the snow levels are approaching record levels. I was wondering how much snow NW Ontario has at this time?It always has an impact on the lake levels for the summmer fishing season.
I was told in the LOTW's area, it's not much. 2 foot or so, which isn't as bad as last years, but we definately need more.
In Ignace we have more than we've had in a couple of years. Running out of places to put it. Water was high in the fall and should be high for opener
